userprompt.name: welcome
userprompt.text:
How Farmers and Consultants are using the Nutrient Management Calculator

  • Estimate nutrient requirements for crops
  • Get feedback on how closely fertilizer and manure applications meet the requirements
  • Enter and download your work confidentially
  • Create pdf reports for farm use
  • Nutrients include nitrogen, phosphorus, and potassium (NPK)
  • Crops include forages, field vegetables, and grains and oilseeds

userprompt.name: disclaimer
userprompt.text: The Province of British Columbia assumes no liability for inaccurate or incomplete information in this web application. Advice provided in this web application does not relieve anyone of their obligations under any legislation.

userprompt.name: agriinfomessage
userprompt.text:
Agronomic Balance

  • considers whether the crop can reach optimal yield and quality
  • soil test values affect crop nutrient requirements
  • considers the nutrients available from manure in the year of application
  • can show if too much N will be applied

userprompt.name: cropinfomessage
userprompt.text:
Crop Removal Balance

  • considers the nutrients removed in the harvested portion of the crop
  • soil test values do not affect crop nutrient removal
  • considers the nutrients available from manure in the long term
  • can show if too much P2O5 will be applied
  • shows potential for soil P or soil K to increase or decrease

userprompt.text:
Calculate Nutrient Balances
  • Add a crop (and the following cover crop, if any) to estimate their nutrient requirements
  • Add nutrient inputs (manure/compost, fertilizer, other) for those crops
  • See recommendations to add more or less nutrients
